    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Media containing any content that is represented in digital form, meaning it is encoded in an electronic format that uses a series of discrete values (commonly the numbers 0 and 1) to record data and render it machine-readable. Digital media include, but are not limited to, digital audio and video tape, floppy discs, and portable hard drives.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
